<br>
 I have set and listened to mages complain about being given a mez spell as they do not consider it to fit in with our class and honestly even though I am not lvl 60 I have a hard time with this logic. We are suppose to be the masters of the elements in this game. If you disagree with that statement then perhaps you need to think back when you were a mage at lvl 51. What are we called? An Elementalist. Therefore is it not to far fetched to think that we should be able to control other elementals that we do not summon? I do not think so if the mage is high enough he should be able to control the strongest elementals that there is for at least short periods of time. <br>
<br>
 Oh course most people would consider my views overpowering to the mage class because I also think we should be given the ability to root elementals in place and also get a down graded versions of the wizard Ice nukes because what is ice made out of? Water and frozen Air? Why is it that a wizard can cast this type of damage spell but the class that is suppose to be the master of the elements can not?<br>
<br>
 Some people consider my views overbalancing and you have the right to think whatever you want. I am sure I am going to get flamed by some wizards on this board but I am not asking for ice nukes that are as strong as a wizard. What I am asking for is Ice based nukes that are in down graded versions of your spells the same way the fire based spells are down graded to yours. <br>
<br>
 I personally think that a mage as defined in EQ as the master of the elements should be able to cast any spell type that any of his pets can cast. Should we get elemental root? yes. Should we get a weaker form of root that is more resistable to handle adds? yes. Should we get the ability to mez elemental mobs? yes. Should we get the ability to cast a down graded version of the wizards ice nukes? Yes.<br>
<br>
think my ideas are unbalanced if you so wish but remember one thing. I and others might not see the class the same way that verant sees it but if they did not want use to be a master over the four basic elements then why did they give us the title of elementalist? <br>
<br>
Something to think about.<br>
<br>
(Ok, let the flaming on me begin)<br>
<br>
Ravenspire Merquise- lvl 54 elementalist of The Praetoriat <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarzan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarzan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#333333>(9/25/02 3:13:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hold Elemental proposed instead of Elemental Silence</span><hr size=1> No worries Raz, it was not a mistake to bring it up. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
